Add UNSD info

Adds fields on UN region, etc.

# first need to separate out multiple countries -- first instance of creating many-to-one for row records
data <- data %>% separate_rows(country, sep = "(,\\s)")

# get unsd data
unsd <- read.csv("C:/DataProjects/fcbc/unsd_m49.csv")

# select data
unsd <- as_tibble(unsd) %>% select(Region.Code:Sub.region.Name, Country.or.Area, M49.Code, ISO.alpha3.Code, Developed...Developing.Countries)

# rename columns
unsd <- unsd %>% rename(country_name = Country.or.Area, region_code = Region.Code, region_name = Region.Name, subregion_code = Sub.region.Code, subregion_name = Sub.region.Name, country_m49 = M49.Code, country_iso3 = ISO.alpha3.Code, development_cat = Developed...Developing.Countries)

# join to data
data <- left_join(data, unsd, by = c("country" = "country_name"))

Data cleanup

Reformat fields

# pop size to integer
data <- data %>% mutate(pop_size = as.integer(gsub(",", "", pop_size)))

Split data

To save memory when going from wide to long

data1 <- data %>% select(pub_id, name, !starts_with(c("env_", "hwb_", "fw_", "use_", "int_", "vca_", "envout_", "hwbout_")))
data2 <- data %>% select(pub_id, name, starts_with(c("env_", "hwb_", "fw_", "use_", "int_", "vca_", "envout_", "hwbout_")))

# pivot longer for partners
data1 <- pivot_longer(data1, starts_with("part_") & !ends_with("part_other"), names_to = "part_type", names_prefix = "(part_)", values_to = "part_log") %>% filter(part_log == TRUE) %>% distinct() %>% select(-part_log)

# create semantic values
data1 <- data1 %>% mutate(part_type = case_when(
  part_type == "localNGO" ~ "NGO local",

))

Results

Results below cover 55 case studies from the Equator Initiative Equator Prize database.

Overview

Countries

# import natural earth country map
map <- sf::st_read("C:/DataProjects/fcbc/countries/ne_110m_admin_0_countries.shp", quiet = TRUE)

# import bounding box
bbox <- sf::st_read("C:/DataProjects/fcbc/bounding_box/ne_110m_wgs84_bounding_box.shp", quiet = TRUE)

# remove unnecessary data
map <- map %>% select(NAME, ISO_A3, CONTINENT, REGION_UN)

# get country counts
counts <- data1 %>% select(pub_id, country_iso3) %>% distinct() %>% group_by(country_iso3) %>% tally(name = "count")

# rename column since multiple by seems unsupported
counts <- counts %>% rename(ISO_A3 = country_iso3)

# join counts
map <- left_join(map, counts, by = "ISO_A3")

# replace NA with O
map <- map %>% replace_na(list(count = 0))

# add factor variable for counts
levels <- c("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")

map <- map %>% mutate(count_cat = factor(case_when(
  count == 0 ~ "0",
  count == 1 ~ "1",
  count == 2 ~ "2",
  count == 3 ~ "3",
  count == 4 ~ "4"
  ), levels = levels))

# set colors
colors <- c("white", RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(4, "YlGnBu"))

# plot map
map.plot <- ggplot(bbox) + 
  geom_sf(fill = "grey95", color = "grey95", size = 0.4) +
  geom_sf(data = map, size = 0.4, aes(fill = count_cat), color = "grey85") + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = colors) + 
  theme_void() + 
  labs(fill = "Case count") + 
  coord_sf(crs = "+proj=eqearth")

# print map
print(map.plot)

Population size

Note: warning below indicates that population info is unspecified for 34 records.

x <- data1 %>% select(pub_id, pop_size) %>% distinct()
k <- nclass.Sturges(x$pop_size)
fill <- "#6baed6"

# plot histogram of all data
p1 <- ggplot(x) + geom_histogram(aes(x = pop_size), bins = k, fill = fill) + theme_minimal() + labs(title = "Histogram of community population ", x = "Population size", y = "Case count", fill = "") + scale_x_continuous(labels = comma)

# plot histogram with outlier removed
x <- data1 %>% select(pub_id, pop_size) %>% filter(pop_size < max(data1$pop_size, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% distinct()
k <- nclass.Sturges(x$pop_size)
p2 <- ggplot(x) + geom_histogram(aes(x = pop_size), bins = k, fill = fill) + theme_minimal() + labs(title = "Histogram of community population (<1,000,000)", x = "Population size", y = "", fill = "") + scale_x_continuous(labels = comma)

# plot grid
plot_grid(p1, p2)
